to develop next-generation technology- Focus research and development effort=
s=20
on integrating current programs regarding hydrogen, fuel cells, and=20
distributed energy.

The NEPD Group recommends that the President direct the Secretary of the=20
Treasury to work with Congress to develop legislation to provide for a=20
temporary income tax credit available for the purchase of new hybrid or=20
fuel-cell vehicles between 2002 and 2007.

The Administration remains committed to the DOT's fuel-cell-powered transit=20
bus program, authored by TEA-21.  This program demonstrates the viability of=
=20
fuel-cell power plants for transit bus applications.

I will update as this moves forward.


